# Sync

Use `skills-seed sync` for the normal day-to-day loop: learn current repository changes and regenerate Skills when needed.

## Purpose

`sync` coordinates:

- Current-file analysis.
- Profile/spec/pattern updates when inputs changed.
- Skill generation when learned output changed or generated files are missing.
- Resume/restart handling for interrupted runs.

Use `sync` first unless the user explicitly wants only learning or only rendering.

## Flags

- `--context`: one-shot text guidance for this run.
- `--context-path`: one-shot guidance loaded from one or more files. Repeatable.
- `--resume`: continue a previous incomplete sync command state.
- `--restart`: clear resumable sync state and start over.
- `--no-interactive`: skip interactive resume/restart prompts.

## Use Cases

- Daily update: `skills-seed sync`
- Automation: `skills-seed sync --no-interactive`
- Resume interrupted sync: `skills-seed sync --resume --no-interactive`
- Ignore partial state: `skills-seed sync --restart`
- Add one-run guidance: `skills-seed sync --context "Focus on payment retry behavior"`
- Load one-run guidance from files: `skills-seed sync --context-path .skills-seed/context/background.md --context-path notes.md`

## Resume Rules

- Use `--resume` only when a previous sync was interrupted and resumable state exists.
- Completed analysis units and their learned results are reused; only unfinished units are analyzed again.
- Use `--restart` when resumable state is stale or should be discarded.
- `--resume` and `--restart` are mutually exclusive.
- A rate-limit retry inside an AI call does not necessarily mean the whole command failed; inspect the final command result and logs.

## Context Boundary

- Use `--context` only for temporary guidance.
- Use `--context-path` when temporary guidance is long or already in a file.
- Move durable repository background into `.skills-seed/context/`.
- Move durable implementation rules into `patterns add/update`.
- Move durable process guidance into `workflow`.

## When Not To Use Sync

- Only update learned state: use `learn current`.
- Only render files from existing state: use `generate skills`.
- Only add a human rule: use `patterns add`, then `generate skills`.
- Only add a process: use `workflow`, then `generate skills`.
